&lt;td&gt;&lt;img src="/articles/0133/1973/sascha1.jpeg" alt="" style="border: 1px solid black; display: block; margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px; margin-top: 5px; margin-bottom: 5px;" width="233"&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;
&lt;strong style="color: #222222; font-family: arial; font-size: small;"&gt;Sascha Meinrath - EUA &lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong style="color: #222222; font-family: arial; font-size: small;"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div style="text-align: justify;"&gt;
&lt;strong style="color: #222222; font-family: arial; font-size: small;"&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style="color: #222222; font-family: arial; font-size: small;"&gt;Pioneiro nas comunidades e cultura da internet, Sascha é vice-presidente da New America Foundation e diretor da Open Technology Institute. Lidera o projeto "Internet in a Suitcase", esforço para popularizar as tecnologias wireless em redes descentralizdas ad hoc (redes mesh). É desse assunto que ele vem falar no FISL15.&lt;/span&gt;
